summary: This document is an FBI 302 report summarizing an interview with a law enforcement officer (likely a detective) regarding the October 20, 2005 search of Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach residence. The officer reviews video and photographs from the search, recalling details about the property, seized items, and missing computers.

events.title: Search of Epstein's Palm Beach Residence
events.description: The Palm Beach Police Department executed a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach residence. Items including message pads and an item labeled 'Twin Torpedoes' were seized.

events.title: Witness Interview/Preparation
events.description: A detective is interviewed/shown evidence (video and photographs) from the 2005 search to refresh his memory and confirm details for the ongoing investigation.

keyFacts: During the 2005 search of Epstein's Palm Beach house, the detective noted that about 80% of the photographs in the house depicted females.
The detective believed it was obvious that computers were missing from the house during the search.
The search included a 'massage room' within the residence and a separate apartment building where an employee lived.
Items seized during the search included message pads and an item labeled 'Twin Torpedoes' (Item #24).
